00:23:07,566 --> 00:23:10,436
after a 30-day grace period
allowing the user time


495
00:23:10,436 --> 00:23:11,476
to purchase their own copy.


496
00:23:12,826 --> 00:23:16,136
On OS X, the app will
need to check the receipt


497
00:23:16,136 --> 00:23:19,046
and once the receipt has
expired after that grace period,


498
00:23:19,046 --> 00:23:20,566
the app can then quit on launch.


499
00:23:20,886 --> 00:23:23,406
And for those of you
OS X app developers not


500
00:23:23,406 --> 00:23:26,106
yet checking receipts, there's
a session later this week


501
00:23:26,106 --> 00:23:26,946
that will teach you how to do it


502
00:23:26,946 --> 00:23:28,826
and I will give you
all the details


503
00:23:28,826 --> 00:23:29,716
at the end of this session.


504
00:23:30,256 --> 00:23:34,466
All right, so that's
the end user experience.


505
00:23:34,896 --> 00:23:38,476
Now, let's talk about what the
MDM product developers will need


506
00:23:38,476 --> 00:23:39,876
to do to support
this new system.


507
00:23:40,346 --> 00:23:43,296
And it really breaks down to
three areas of functionality.


508
00:23:43,816 --> 00:23:46,516
First, authenticating this
organization's account


509
00:23:46,606 --> 00:23:48,296
with the Volume Purchase
Program,


510
00:23:49,986 --> 00:23:53,066
sending a user an invitation
to link their Apple ID


511
00:23:53,066 --> 00:23:55,026
to your organization
and I'll talk much more


512
00:23:55,026 --> 00:23:55,816
about that in a moment.


513
00:23:56,016 --> 00:23:57,626
And then of course the
heart of the matter,


514
00:23:57,906 --> 00:24:00,766
being able to assign licenses,
to be able to revoke them


515
00:24:00,976 --> 00:24:02,566
and then assign into
some other user.


516
00:24:03,146 --> 00:24:05,726
So let's talk about
each one in turn.


517
00:24:07,136 --> 00:24:09,936
The organization will
obtain a secure token


518
00:24:10,086 --> 00:24:12,136
from the VPP website
where they're going


519
00:24:12,136 --> 00:24:14,096
to purchase their
content in bulk.


520
00:24:15,306 --> 00:24:17,106
This works great because
then you don't have


521
00:24:17,106 --> 00:24:18,966
to store their credentials
for them, you just need


522
00:24:18,966 --> 00:24:21,476
to provide URI for them
to enter their token.


523
00:24:22,086 --> 00:24:24,846
It's relatively long-lived
but will currently plan


524
00:24:24,846 --> 00:24:26,096
to expire after a year.


525
00:24:26,246 --> 00:24:27,456
So, it is something
that they will have


526
00:24:27,456 --> 00:24:29,416
to do periodically
but not frequently.


527
00:24:31,626 --> 00:24:33,026
Now, user invitations.


528
00:24:33,366 --> 00:24:35,476
This is a really
important part of the system


529
00:24:35,476 --> 00:24:36,866
that preserves user privacy.


530
00:24:38,156 --> 00:24:41,186
We don't want to force users to
reveal their private Apple ID


531
00:24:41,256 --> 00:24:43,246
to the organization or
the school that's going


532
00:24:43,246 --> 00:24:44,886
to provide them with
this content.


533
00:24:45,726 --> 00:24:48,346
So there's a one-time
process to link their Apple ID


534
00:24:48,346 --> 00:24:51,376
with the organization providing
content in the iTunes Store.


535
00:24:52,676 --> 00:24:56,666
The MDM server will request
an individual URL for the user


536
00:24:56,666 --> 00:25:00,736
that they are tracking in their
system and then be able to use


537
00:25:00,736 --> 00:25:02,446
that URL to construct
an invitation


538
00:25:02,446 --> 00:25:05,436
and they can send it via
email, construct a web portal,


539
00:25:05,746 --> 00:25:08,686
or send it over MDM, which
we think is the best approach


540
00:25:08,686 --> 00:25:10,556
if the user has a
device enrolled


541
00:25:10,936 --> 00:25:14,436
that the MDM server knows about
and we'll show that later on.


542
00:25:15,616 --> 00:25:18,046
Finally, the process


543
00:25:18,046 --> 00:25:19,536
of the assigning license
couldn't be easier.


544
00:25:19,866 --> 00:25:22,056
The MDM server can--
once it's authenticated,


545
00:25:22,056 --> 00:25:25,476
the account with the iTunes
Store can request the list


546
00:25:25,476 --> 00:25:28,236
of app and book purchases
that organization has made.


547
00:25:29,206 --> 00:25:31,566
They can send request to
say assign this list of apps


548
00:25:31,566 --> 00:25:33,116
and books to these
lists of users.


549
00:25:34,486 --> 00:25:37,626
And then, if desired,
that's already sufficient


550
00:25:37,626 --> 00:25:40,006
to get the content out to
those users, but if they want


551
00:25:40,006 --> 00:25:42,816
to tell the device to
install the app on the device,


552
00:25:43,236 --> 00:25:45,446
they can send the
MDM command out.


553
00:25:46,666 --> 00:25:48,576
Revocations are the opposite.


554
00:25:48,606 --> 00:25:51,486
They can send a list of
revoked licenses for this app


555
00:25:52,676 --> 00:25:54,406
from these lists of users.


556
00:25:55,406 --> 00:25:59,536
However, book assignments
just like code based model,


557
00:25:59,536 --> 00:26:02,226
it's still permanent, a
transfer of ownership.


558
00:26:02,616 --> 00:26:04,706
We decide to add that
to the new system


559
00:26:04,706 --> 00:26:07,446
because that will enable
MDM providers as well


560
00:26:07,446 --> 00:26:10,006
as organizations to use the
same system to manage both types


561
00:26:10,006 --> 00:26:12,296
of content, but for
now at least,


562
00:26:12,606 --> 00:26:13,846
book assignments are permanent.


563
00:26:14,356 --> 00:26:17,296
All right, let me
give you a short--


564
00:26:17,386 --> 00:26:19,246
walk you through a short
architecture diagram


565
00:26:19,246 --> 00:26:20,466
to give you another
way of thinking


566
00:26:20,466 --> 00:26:21,706
about the way the system works.


567
00:26:22,396 --> 00:26:24,926
Each organization will go
to the [inaudible] website


568
00:26:24,926 --> 00:26:27,256
and purchase whatever
app and book licenses


569
00:26:27,256 --> 00:26:28,106
that they wish to have.


570
00:26:28,826 --> 00:26:30,826
That information flows
into the iTunes Store.


571
00:26:32,206 --> 00:26:35,496
The MDM server can query the
iTunes Store for those licenses


572
00:26:36,086 --> 00:26:38,686
and then send up requests
to make assignments.


573
00:26:39,236 --> 00:26:42,646
Once that's been done, the
device can check in with the--


574
00:26:42,756 --> 00:26:44,036
the device will be notified


575
00:26:44,166 --> 00:26:47,566
to pull its Purchased
list and update its UI.


576
00:26:48,336 --> 00:26:51,246
At that time, again, the user
can freely download those


577
00:26:51,246 --> 00:26:56,336
assigned apps and books or the
MDM server can send the command


578
00:26:56,466 --> 00:27:00,396
down to the device to tell it
to download particular book


579
00:27:00,396 --> 00:27:03,006
or books-- sorry,
particular app or apps.


