00:29:50,976 --> 00:29:55,116
And then finally, the pair-- the
one that I showed you an example


643
00:29:55,116 --> 00:29:56,506
of that actually
assigns a license


644
00:29:56,556 --> 00:29:59,066
to a user and then revokes it.


645
00:30:00,496 --> 00:30:02,176
There are a few additional
services


646
00:30:02,176 --> 00:30:04,636
that performs an important
housekeeping tasks including


647
00:30:04,636 --> 00:30:06,406
if you want to update
any of the user metadata,


648
00:30:06,406 --> 00:30:09,266
if you want to store
some additional metadata


649
00:30:09,266 --> 00:30:14,736
for the organization, and if
