00:30:21,076 --> 00:30:22,776
and disassociate
their iTunes account


653
00:30:22,936 --> 00:30:25,616
which will also revoke any
revocable licenses currently


654
00:30:25,616 --> 00:30:26,516
assigned to that user.


655
00:30:27,506 --> 00:30:31,006
You can of course later reinvite
that retired user if desired


656
00:30:32,376 --> 00:30:35,386
by passing along their
previous user string


657
00:30:35,776 --> 00:30:37,566
to the registered service.


658
00:30:38,606 --> 00:30:40,436
Now, I mentioned earlier
there are a number


659
00:30:40,436 --> 00:30:42,256
of different user
concepts within the system.


660
00:30:42,376 --> 00:30:43,906
So let's talk about that now.


661
00:30:44,676 --> 00:30:47,716
The first is your MDM
solutions idea of the user.


662
00:30:48,346 --> 00:30:51,276
That's represented in the system
by the client user ID string,


663
00:30:51,996 --> 00:30:53,716
which is typically
going to be a UUID


664
00:30:53,926 --> 00:30:55,876
and this may be the
representation coming


665
00:30:55,876 --> 00:30:58,116
out of the directory
that's feeding users


666
00:30:58,116 --> 00:30:59,276
in groups into your solution.


667
00:31:00,296 --> 00:31:03,366
The second is the VPP--


668
00:31:03,366 --> 00:31:05,536
the Volume Purchase
Programs ID of the user.


669
00:31:05,536 --> 00:31:07,286
And that's represented
by the user ID.


670
00:31:08,706 --> 00:31:10,566
Finally, there's
the user's Apple ID,


671
00:31:10,766 --> 00:31:13,356
which again we don't want to
reveal to the MDM solution


672
00:31:13,356 --> 00:31:14,276
and the organization,


673
00:31:14,566 --> 00:31:18,286
so you will receive
Hash of that Apple ID.


674
00:31:18,916 --> 00:31:21,326
So there's three kinds
of users can be combined


675
00:31:21,326 --> 00:31:23,686
at the two different key forms
or the ways that represent--


676
00:31:23,686 --> 00:31:25,846
or referring to a
particular user.


677
00:31:26,686 --> 00:31:28,716
The user ID is just
a single long


678
00:31:29,636 --> 00:31:33,076
and then the other form is tuple
of the client user ID string,


679
00:31:33,076 --> 00:31:36,446
again typically UUID and
the Hash of the Apple ID.


680
00:31:37,106 --> 00:31:40,166
Now, these two key forms
have a one-to-one association


681
00:31:40,166 --> 00:31:42,756
at any one given time,
but that's not immutable,


682
00:31:43,056 --> 00:31:47,116
that link can change if a
user is retired and reinvited.


683
00:31:47,116 --> 00:31:51,346
So, let's talk a little
about the user ID key form.


684
00:31:51,926 --> 00:31:53,656
This one is very easy
to track as it's just


685
00:31:53,656 --> 00:31:58,276
that one single long
integer, and as I mentioned,


686
00:31:58,276 --> 00:32:01,386
it's always tied to exactly
one client user ID string


687
00:32:01,656 --> 00:32:05,216
but that reference can
change, and in fact can change


688
00:32:05,216 --> 00:32:07,076
when the user accepts
the invitation.


689
00:32:07,646 --> 00:32:11,076
So, I'm going to illustrate that
again with a little diagram.


690
00:32:11,516 --> 00:32:15,296
So, at this point, the
MDM solution has its idea


691
00:32:15,296 --> 00:32:19,466
of what this user's UUID
is from their directory


692
00:32:19,536 --> 00:32:21,806
and has called the
register service


693
00:32:21,876 --> 00:32:25,546
to obtain an individualized
URL for that user,


694
00:32:26,006 --> 00:32:27,956
which now is identified
with user ID2 .


695
00:32:28,716 --> 00:32:30,456
That invitation sent
out to the user


696
00:32:30,976 --> 00:32:34,626
and when the user accepts it,
the MDM server will be provided


697
00:32:34,626 --> 00:32:37,196
with the Hash of that Apple ID.


698
00:32:37,626 --> 00:32:39,796
Now, let's imagine that
for whatever reason


699
00:32:39,796 --> 00:32:44,336
that user is retired, and in
fact this is not the first time


700
00:32:44,336 --> 00:32:46,476
that this has happened,
there was a former user ID1,


701
00:32:46,476 --> 00:32:52,906
but now retired that link,
generate a new invitation


702
00:32:52,906 --> 00:32:55,816
for user ID3 which could be
sent out to the user again


703
00:32:56,146 --> 00:32:58,866
which could accept-- who could
accept it with the same Apple ID


704
00:32:58,866 --> 00:32:59,896
or different Apple ID.


705
00:33:00,436 --> 00:33:04,266
Now, let's talk about
the other key form based


706
00:33:04,266 --> 00:33:07,716
on the MDM's servers
idea of the user.


707
00:33:08,246 --> 00:33:11,506
Now, this more directly
maps between the MDM user


708
00:33:11,506 --> 00:33:16,986
and the Apple ID be it Hash.


709
00:33:17,196 --> 00:33:19,236
What you'll see is that
that hash will be null


710
00:33:19,236 --> 00:33:21,356
until the end user has
accepted the invitation.


711
00:33:22,076 --> 00:33:24,976
Once the user has accepted the
invitation that hash uniquely


